1
00:01:01,327 --> 00:01:02,760
"My name is Michelle McNally"

2
00:01:03,363 --> 00:01:06,355
"The older child of an Anglo Indian
family based in Shimla"

3
00:01:09,636 --> 00:01:12,434
"This story is about me and my teacher"

4
00:01:13,406 --> 00:01:16,136
"A story about two people
left incomplete by god..."

5
00:01:16,976 --> 00:01:18,967
"who have fought a battle with fate..."

6
00:01:19,312 --> 00:01:21,371
"and made the impossible, possible"

7
00:01:22,549 --> 00:01:24,744
"The world in my story is different..."

8
00:01:26,086 --> 00:01:29,078
"where sound transcends into silence..."

9
00:01:32,058 --> 00:01:34,788
"and light into darkness"

10
00:01:36,863 --> 00:01:38,057
"This is my world"

11
00:01:38,698 --> 00:01:42,566
"Where nothing can be seen nor heard"

12
00:01:43,670 --> 00:01:47,629
"There is only one name for my world..."

13
00:02:00,086 --> 00:02:02,486
"How long can you live in this darkness?"

14
00:02:03,156 --> 00:02:06,956
"A few moments... hours... days?"

15
00:02:08,361 --> 00:02:11,455
"For 40 years I've lived
in this darkness..."

16
00:02:12,265 --> 00:02:15,428
"for 4 years I've given
my final B.A. Exam..."

17
00:02:16,503 --> 00:02:19,301
"and for twelve years, I've gone
to this church, every Sunday"

18
00:02:20,974 --> 00:02:22,703
"But that Sunday was special"

19
00:02:23,343 --> 00:02:26,642
"I felt God would answer my prayers..."

20
00:03:03,550 --> 00:03:06,110
"...my only prayer was..."

21
00:03:06,619 --> 00:03:10,316
"...that my teacher
would come back to me"

22
00:03:13,126 --> 00:03:18,063
"My prayers take long to reach God..."

23
00:03:19,165 --> 00:03:22,157
"and He takes long in granting them"

24
00:03:23,870 --> 00:03:25,804
"Even that Sunday I didn't
find my teacher"

25
00:03:27,006 --> 00:03:29,031
"That evening Sara and I were
returning home..."

26
00:03:29,542 --> 00:03:30,338
"...when suddenly..."

27
00:03:43,990 --> 00:03:44,786
Wait...

28
00:03:48,561 --> 00:03:50,495
Michelle, just wait for me, ok?

29
00:04:21,127 --> 00:04:21,923
Oh my God!

30
00:04:23,329 --> 00:04:28,289
MICHELLE!! MICHELLE!!

31
00:04:29,969 --> 00:04:33,097
MICHELLE!!
Your prayers have been answered...

32
00:04:34,240 --> 00:04:36,640
it's Debraj... he's there
near the fountain,

33
00:04:38,411 --> 00:04:44,441
It's true, I promise, yes promise!
Come! Yes. Yes

34
00:05:08,675 --> 00:05:11,007
"That day my teacher came back to me..."

35
00:05:11,911 --> 00:05:14,505
"after 12 years I recognized him..."

36
00:05:14,881 --> 00:05:18,874
"but he had forgotten everything..."

37
00:05:20,286 --> 00:05:24,222
"even me"

38
00:05:24,957 --> 00:05:27,926
"I am writing this story for him..."

39
00:05:28,161 --> 00:05:30,561
"to my teacher - Debraj Sahai"

40
00:05:56,889 --> 00:05:58,857
He doesn't remember anything?

41
00:05:59,726 --> 00:06:01,455
Surely there must be something
we can do.

42
00:06:01,828 --> 00:06:06,231
Sara, Mr. Sahai has Alzheimer's disease.

43
00:06:06,499 --> 00:06:09,559
He has forgotten everything.
It's a very scary void.

44
00:06:10,036 --> 00:06:13,301
Mr. Sahai has even forgotten his bed.

45
00:06:13,573 --> 00:06:18,340
He has forgotten words,
even forgotten how to speak.

46
00:06:20,713 --> 00:06:23,375
No doctor. I refuse to believe this...

47
00:06:24,050 --> 00:06:25,677
he must remember something...

48
00:06:26,352 --> 00:06:30,152
otherwise, after all these years,
to find him at our house...

49
00:06:32,058 --> 00:06:34,959
and Mr. Sahai can
never forget Michelle.

50
00:06:36,195 --> 00:06:39,187
Like a duster wipes the words
of a blackboard...

51
00:06:39,932 --> 00:06:44,426
the disease has slowly
wiped out all his memories.

52
00:06:44,971 --> 00:06:50,068
A few words or instances
might spark some memory...

53
00:06:50,743 --> 00:06:52,370
but Alzheimer's has no cure.

54
00:06:54,013 --> 00:06:55,071
What is Michelle doing?

55
00:06:56,482 --> 00:07:00,350
She wants to read to him
her life story, in Braille.

56
00:07:01,721 --> 00:07:07,353
Maybe by touching those words
he might remember something...

57
00:07:08,227 --> 00:07:11,458
Michelle believes
that this miracle will happen.

58
00:07:16,436 --> 00:07:18,063
Science doesn't believe in miracles.

59
00:07:18,638 --> 00:07:20,606
It is impossible for him
to remember anything...

60
00:07:20,940 --> 00:07:26,105
Impossible is one word that
Mr. Sahai never taught Michelle

61
00:07:27,380 --> 00:07:29,848
And what you call impossible...

62
00:07:30,650 --> 00:07:33,141
she will make possible.

63
00:07:34,053 --> 00:07:36,578
"You were written in my destiny..."

64
00:07:36,956 --> 00:07:38,583
"when I was 2 years old"

65
00:07:38,958 --> 00:07:46,694
"That night suddenly
all happiness left us..."

66
00:07:47,366 --> 00:07:49,334
"when my life entered a black vaccuum"

67
00:07:49,769 --> 00:07:54,297
Michelle... my beautiful baby.

68
00:07:54,941 --> 00:07:58,604
You're not sick anymore...
now you can play in water.

69
00:08:01,113 --> 00:08:05,948
Look who has come! Papa!
What has the doctor told papa?

70
00:08:06,285 --> 00:08:10,153
The doctor has said that
Michelle can't see or hear.

71
00:08:15,294 --> 00:08:16,318
What did you say?

72
00:08:17,930 --> 00:08:20,194
Our Michelle has gone
blind and deaf.

73
00:08:36,482 --> 00:08:39,246
Look at me! Michelle!

74
00:09:10,216 --> 00:09:12,184
"I was like an animal"

75
00:09:12,919 --> 00:09:15,251
"Children loved playing pranks on me."

76
00:09:16,122 --> 00:09:17,885
"So did God."

77
00:09:18,858 --> 00:09:22,157
Mrs. Gomes! Who has tied
these cans on Michelle?

78
00:09:24,297 --> 00:09:26,492
Shh... calm down Michelle,
calm down, baby calm down.

79
00:09:42,682 --> 00:09:44,877
Fire! Fire! Mrs. McNally. Fire!

80
00:09:45,084 --> 00:09:48,986
Help Mrs. McNally
Help. Mrs. McNally

81
00:09:53,092 --> 00:09:56,425
For eight years... every day
a new accident

82
00:09:56,562 --> 00:09:59,895
Hurting someone with a knife,
or breaking her own head!

83
00:10:00,166 --> 00:10:01,827
She could have burnt
the whole house down.

84
00:10:02,034 --> 00:10:04,969
With Michelle, we can never be happy.

85
00:10:05,171 --> 00:10:06,433
What are you trying to say?

86
00:10:06,639 --> 00:10:09,472
We will send her to an institution.

87
00:10:09,875 --> 00:10:12,867
You mean a mental asylum?

88
00:10:13,913 --> 00:10:16,245
How can you think that?

89
00:10:16,449 --> 00:10:19,509
Cathy, I love her just as much.

90
00:10:19,785 --> 00:10:21,116
But I still want to send her away.

91
00:10:21,754 --> 00:10:24,086
She could cause irreparable damage.

92
00:10:24,290 --> 00:10:26,884
No. I'm sorry. I don't agree.

93
00:10:27,093 --> 00:10:29,561
There is no other solution.

94
00:10:29,762 --> 00:10:32,322
I have no more patience left.

95
00:10:33,532 --> 00:10:36,990
Sara! Oh my God!

96
00:10:37,837 --> 00:10:41,671
Enough of this!
This child will be the death of us.

97
00:10:42,341 --> 00:10:43,000
Paul, leave her!

98
00:10:43,209 --> 00:10:47,168
She will not stay her another moment.
She almost... killed Sara.

99
00:10:50,449 --> 00:10:53,384
Let her go!

100
00:10:53,552 --> 00:11:00,788
It's not her fault.
For God's sake!

101
00:11:01,293 --> 00:11:03,124
Try and understand her.

102
00:11:04,930 --> 00:11:07,694
She is suffering.

103
00:11:10,503 --> 00:11:13,370
She is suffocating
in her own darkness.

104
00:11:16,509 --> 00:11:18,033
My baby is suffering

105
00:11:27,253 --> 00:11:29,346
There's this school in Dehradun...

106
00:11:30,022 --> 00:11:33,048
where children like Michelle
are given special training.

107
00:11:33,626 --> 00:11:36,390
If you let me,
I can write for a teacher...

108
00:11:36,595 --> 00:11:38,495
We do not need a teacher...

109
00:11:39,231 --> 00:11:40,425
We need a magician.

110
00:11:41,434 --> 00:11:45,461
I don't want to hear anymore
that there is no cure for our Michelle.

111
00:11:45,671 --> 00:11:46,933
One Last time Paul.

112
00:11:47,973 --> 00:11:49,838
Maybe this is the teacher
who is the magician...

113
00:11:50,543 --> 00:11:53,410
who will bring light
into our Michelle's life.

114
00:12:04,957 --> 00:12:05,719
Debraj.

115
00:12:07,727 --> 00:12:14,223
Ah, Ms. Nair. Come into the light.

116
00:12:15,634 --> 00:12:19,229
What are you doing, Debraj?
You've just had your eyes operated.

117
00:12:19,438 --> 00:12:22,601
And now what are you doing
holding a dying bulb?

118
00:12:22,975 --> 00:12:27,207
This bulb is dying, Ms. Nair.
I need to stand by it

119
00:12:29,048 --> 00:12:29,514
Am I right?

120
00:12:32,118 --> 00:12:35,349
It's... it's dying.

121
00:12:39,125 --> 00:12:41,616
You've been drinking again all day.
Haven't you, Debraj?

122
00:12:41,827 --> 00:12:43,351
No, no...

123
00:12:44,663 --> 00:12:49,566
Trying to find a sign for light.
For my deaf and blind children...

124
00:12:51,270 --> 00:12:53,932
whose light has been
taken away from them.

125
00:12:54,006 --> 00:13:03,039
Light... LIGHT!

126
00:13:03,382 --> 00:13:08,149
Just spell it, Debraj.
L.I.G.H.T. Light

127
00:13:08,354 --> 00:13:12,051
Ah! The difference between
a teacher... and a magician.

128
00:13:12,691 --> 00:13:14,886
You make me so angry sometimes Debraj.

129
00:13:15,161 --> 00:13:17,129
Angry... Angry

130
00:13:17,630 --> 00:13:19,154
Stop this bullshit

131
00:13:19,365 --> 00:13:23,802
Bullshit Bullshit
Bull. Bull... Bull... shit Bull... shit

132
00:13:24,003 --> 00:13:29,498
I do not have time for your talks.
I have some very important news for you.

133
00:13:29,708 --> 00:13:35,374
Three guesses... if it's my termination
letter, put it in the third drawer.

134
00:13:35,581 --> 00:13:37,549
If it's my last salary,
then it goes here in my pocket...

135
00:13:37,750 --> 00:13:41,117
and if it's a notice to vacate this room
then throw it in the dustbin.

136
00:13:41,320 --> 00:13:44,187
And. On your way to any of
these Ms Nair... could you please

137
00:13:44,390 --> 00:13:47,450
fetch me my... eye-drops... from that
table over there. Thank you.

138
00:13:47,660 --> 00:13:49,560
You may have three guesses Debraj...

139
00:13:49,829 --> 00:13:52,423
but you have only one choice.
This letter.

140
00:13:53,365 --> 00:13:56,596
An eight-year girl,
in Shimla, Michelle.

141
00:13:57,403 --> 00:14:01,203
She can't see, she can't hear and
her parents don't understand her.

142
00:14:02,241 --> 00:14:04,209
You are their last hope Debraj.

143
00:14:05,010 --> 00:14:06,773
Otherwise they will put her
in the asylum.

144
00:14:07,146 --> 00:14:11,845
You are the best teacher I know.
She needs a teacher, you need a job.

145
00:14:12,451 --> 00:14:12,940
Look up

146
00:14:16,322 --> 00:14:18,381
What do you see in this eye, Ms. Nair?

147
00:14:20,025 --> 00:14:21,049
A great love for me.

148
00:14:21,327 --> 00:14:23,488
You need to get your eyes checked.

149
00:14:27,800 --> 00:14:29,893
And this one?
- Nothing

150
00:14:30,369 --> 00:14:32,132
Her name is Michelle, isn't it?

151
00:14:36,842 --> 00:14:38,469
I can see everything clearly.

152
00:14:40,679 --> 00:14:42,340
A beautiful morning...

153
00:14:44,149 --> 00:14:45,639
snow covered streets...

154
00:14:47,052 --> 00:14:48,519
and that little girl...

155
00:14:49,521 --> 00:14:53,548
a lost soul, directionless.

156
00:14:54,593 --> 00:15:00,395
I will give her wings
made of words, Ms. Nair.

157
00:15:01,100 --> 00:15:03,933
I will teach her how to fly.

158
00:15:04,136 --> 00:15:10,200
You couldn't do anything for yourself
and you're out to change others' lives

159
00:15:11,076 --> 00:15:13,772
What happened, do your eyes hurt?

160
00:15:13,979 --> 00:15:17,278
No, not my eyes...

161
00:15:18,651 --> 00:15:23,145
my heart hurts...

162
00:15:28,928 --> 00:15:37,028
listening to your cruel words...

163
00:15:39,004 --> 00:15:46,308
it hurts... it hurts!

164
00:15:49,848 --> 00:15:53,249
That after spending thirty years
in this school...

165
00:15:53,452 --> 00:16:01,325
I'm just an unseen unheard entity.

166
00:16:03,028 --> 00:16:08,364
When I saw the school
for the last time...

167
00:16:08,667 --> 00:16:14,765
my students were waving to me
in the wrong direction.

168
00:16:17,676 --> 00:16:22,238
Waving to me in the
wrong direction Ms. Nair.

169
00:16:25,217 --> 00:16:30,917
Oh! Lt... it... it... hurts...

170
00:16:34,159 --> 00:16:34,853
it hurts.

171
00:16:41,867 --> 00:16:44,131
"Destiny had put together
two strange soul- mates."

172
00:16:45,337 --> 00:16:47,931
"I was left incomplete by god..."

173
00:16:49,208 --> 00:16:51,870
"and you were
a battle - weary warrior."

174
00:16:55,814 --> 00:16:57,645
"I was waiting in my darkness..."

175
00:16:58,784 --> 00:17:01,275
"and you were bringing
the flickering light."

176
00:17:11,497 --> 00:17:14,193
Right. Where's the girl?

177
00:17:14,666 --> 00:17:17,794
This is all we needed.
An alcoholic teacher.

178
00:17:22,207 --> 00:17:29,978
Mmmm... lnteresting.
Playful, bit of a brat.

179
00:17:34,586 --> 00:17:35,712
And very pretty...

180
00:17:55,274 --> 00:17:59,768
Yes. Yes... someone new...
a new buddy.

181
00:18:07,686 --> 00:18:13,283
You like my glasses, don't you?
Well... you can have them...

182
00:18:14,026 --> 00:18:16,426
here... there you go.

183
00:18:21,733 --> 00:18:22,358
Happy?

184
00:18:26,004 --> 00:18:28,973
Teacher... Tea... cher

185
00:18:32,411 --> 00:18:34,777
Mr. Sahai, she understands?

186
00:18:34,980 --> 00:18:38,006
No, she's just imitating me.

187
00:18:38,317 --> 00:18:41,775
Good... good girl

188
00:18:49,261 --> 00:18:49,886
What is she doing?

189
00:18:50,129 --> 00:18:53,292
That's her sign for me.
Her mother

190
00:18:53,499 --> 00:18:58,994
Oh, she's strong.
- I'm really sorry, Mr. Sahai

191
00:18:59,204 --> 00:19:00,000
It's alright.

192
00:19:02,407 --> 00:19:05,604
What's this!!
What is this bell for?

193
00:19:05,911 --> 00:19:07,606
This is her identity

194
00:19:08,080 --> 00:19:10,844
If she is lost.
We find her through its sound.

195
00:19:11,884 --> 00:19:13,078
Take it off!!!!

196
00:19:17,222 --> 00:19:20,749
When you think, that
your child is an animal...

197
00:19:20,893 --> 00:19:26,763
what do you expect of others?
- It's your job to make her human.

198
00:19:27,466 --> 00:19:29,161
How do you plan to do this?

199
00:19:30,469 --> 00:19:31,697
These Fingers, Mr. McNally.

200
00:19:33,338 --> 00:19:34,635
They're eyes of the blind...

201
00:19:35,440 --> 00:19:36,634
...Voice of the mute...

202
00:19:37,809 --> 00:19:39,299
poetry of the deaf.

203
00:19:41,346 --> 00:19:43,246
Raise it to a sword...

204
00:19:44,016 --> 00:19:45,643
...clench it for strength.

205
00:19:46,552 --> 00:19:47,849
They can feed you and slap you,

206
00:19:48,587 --> 00:19:50,350
They can point you towards God
and sometimes...

207
00:19:50,622 --> 00:19:51,316
even the door.

208
00:19:53,492 --> 00:19:59,397
It isn't as easy as you make it seem.
My daughter is like me...

209
00:19:59,932 --> 00:20:01,866
stubborn...
- Insolent.

210
00:20:03,335 --> 00:20:05,098
Not you. Your daughter

211
00:20:05,304 --> 00:20:07,966
Lunch... will be served
shortly, Mr. Sahai.

212
00:20:08,340 --> 00:20:10,570
Thank you. Mrs. McNally,
I'm so hungry.

213
00:20:19,651 --> 00:20:21,676
Thank you Lord, for the bread
on our plate

214
00:20:22,854 --> 00:20:26,449
for the air we breathe,
so fresh and pure.

215
00:20:26,992 --> 00:20:29,825
For kindness and faith,
we are thankful to Thee.

216
00:20:30,963 --> 00:20:35,457
Life's treasures and loved ones,
we hold and cherish.

217
00:20:45,978 --> 00:20:46,910
No

218
00:20:47,312 --> 00:20:49,212
Leave her, Mr. Sahai.

219
00:20:49,548 --> 00:20:52,346
No. She has to learn how to behave.

220
00:20:52,784 --> 00:20:55,344
Leave her hand Mr. Sahai!

221
00:20:55,554 --> 00:20:58,819
This is the only reason
she hasn't learnt anything.

222
00:20:59,758 --> 00:21:03,387
I will not tolerate this
in front of my guests.

223
00:21:03,562 --> 00:21:06,463
Michelle eats like this.

224
00:21:07,532 --> 00:21:10,899
Either she eats from her plate
or stays hungry. Am I understood?

225
00:21:11,637 --> 00:21:14,538
Let her eat, you will
get another plate.

226
00:21:14,740 --> 00:21:18,198
I... don't have a problem
with the plate, Mr. McNally.

227
00:21:18,410 --> 00:21:20,037
The plate... is fine.

228
00:21:20,245 --> 00:21:22,440
Let her go.
This is no way to teach.

229
00:21:22,648 --> 00:21:25,276
Don't you feel pity
for this handicapped child?

230
00:21:25,584 --> 00:21:30,385
Pity? And on this devil?
So she can do as she pleases?

231
00:21:30,589 --> 00:21:32,784
No Mr. McNally,
I have pity on you...

232
00:21:32,991 --> 00:21:34,959
and don't you dare
call her handicapped.

233
00:21:35,160 --> 00:21:41,588
That's enough! Do not forget that you
are a paid servant in this house.

234
00:21:41,800 --> 00:21:45,964
A Teacher! Mr. McNally... not a
paid servant... A paid teacher.

235
00:21:46,171 --> 00:21:48,071
Leave her, right now.

236
00:21:48,273 --> 00:21:49,638
No! You leave. All of you.

237
00:21:49,841 --> 00:21:51,399
Mr. Sahai,
handling Michelle like this...

238
00:21:51,610 --> 00:21:54,738
Mrs. McNally... you had said that
you'd cooperate.

239
00:21:55,013 --> 00:21:56,810
All right. There's no point in
going on like this.

240
00:21:57,015 --> 00:21:59,813
Let's give him a chance.
Let him do his job Paul.

241
00:22:00,018 --> 00:22:03,647
Leave! Leave!

242
00:22:18,470 --> 00:22:20,938
Martha, I'm really sorry,
for today's lunch

243
00:22:21,139 --> 00:22:22,606
Don't worry Cathy.

244
00:22:22,841 --> 00:22:25,935
He's a new teacher, that's why.
Isn't it, Paul?

245
00:22:26,411 --> 00:22:28,106
Martha, I'll drop you home.

246
00:22:30,882 --> 00:22:32,076
Paul, I will speak to Mr. Sahai...

247
00:22:37,789 --> 00:22:40,349
I am very hungry;
I am going to eat...

248
00:22:41,293 --> 00:22:45,627
and if you behave
then you can eat too.

249
00:23:02,280 --> 00:23:02,837
Spoon!

250
00:23:06,017 --> 00:23:09,248
No. You will not use
your hands to eat your food.

251
