00:45:26,190 --> 00:45:27,748
I will not give up so easily.

496
00:45:27,958 --> 00:45:29,892
I have kept my promise.
Now it's your turn.

497
00:45:30,094 --> 00:45:33,586
But it's not yet over Mrs. McNally.
There are still a few minutes left.

498
00:45:33,797 --> 00:45:36,493
Paul can come at any moment.
Mr. Sahai. I'm helpless

499
00:45:36,700 --> 00:45:38,167
Yes. Mrs. McNally.
But she has to learn.

500
00:45:38,368 --> 00:45:40,359
Mr. Sahai...
- She has to learn...

501
00:45:40,571 --> 00:45:45,508
that the hand she is holding has a name.
That you are mother, mother...

502
00:45:46,310 --> 00:45:49,905
M.O.T.H.E. R... mother.

503
00:45:55,419 --> 00:45:56,249
And that is FATHER.

504
00:46:00,891 --> 00:46:03,086
Paul, I was just...
- Leave, Mr. Sahai.

505
00:46:29,019 --> 00:46:31,852
Dear Ms. Nair, you will be
delighted to know...

506
00:46:32,055 --> 00:46:37,118
that after having spent 20 days
with little Michelle, I have failed.

507
00:46:38,195 --> 00:46:42,393
However, if you're smiling at the
thought of looking into my eyes again...

508
00:46:43,100 --> 00:46:44,624
you are terribly mistaken.

509
00:46:55,112 --> 00:46:57,239
Mrs. Gomes, will you stop her?

510
00:46:57,881 --> 00:47:01,146
Let her be Mr. Sahai.
She's very happy today

511
00:47:05,055 --> 00:47:07,751
No! Stop it Michelle.
You little brat.

512
00:47:09,393 --> 00:47:11,258
I am not going to allow you
to do this to me.

513
00:47:13,030 --> 00:47:14,497
I might have been asked to leave...

514
00:47:14,698 --> 00:47:18,395
but I am not going to leave you
to behave like this.

515
00:47:22,906 --> 00:47:24,840
Stop it Michelle.
Stop it!

516
00:47:25,042 --> 00:47:28,603
You won't forget what I've
taught you in 20 days... sit down

517
00:47:28,812 --> 00:47:29,278
Please leave her Mr. Sahai,
let her be.

518
00:47:29,479 --> 00:47:30,639
Sit... sit down.

519
00:47:31,348 --> 00:47:36,684
You will use this napkin on your
neck and use a spoon... to eat.

520
00:47:36,887 --> 00:47:39,185
Mo you are not going to throw...

521
00:48:02,346 --> 00:48:03,745
Come on, Come here...

522
00:48:04,948 --> 00:48:08,247
You brat... you want to
throw water at me!

523
00:48:08,719 --> 00:48:12,780
Let me teach you what water is!
Come here! What water is, come on!

524
00:48:13,824 --> 00:48:19,490
This is water... water... water...

525
00:48:19,696 --> 00:48:24,497
Give me your hand... This is woah...
Water... water... Understand?

526
00:48:24,701 --> 00:48:25,326
Woah!!

527
00:48:29,806 --> 00:48:30,329
Woah!

528
00:49:50,721 --> 00:49:54,316
Water... it's water...

529
00:49:54,558 --> 00:49:59,689
W.A.T.E.R.

530
00:50:22,419 --> 00:50:23,511
Mrs. McNally!!!

531
00:50:30,994 --> 00:50:36,933
Yes... this is 'Grass'.
G.R.A.S.S. Spell it...

532
00:50:39,569 --> 00:50:42,060
Very good... Very good...
Mrs. McNally!!!

533
00:50:43,774 --> 00:50:50,646
That's 'FLOWER' flower...
flower... F.L.O.W.E. R... flower.

534
00:50:51,014 --> 00:50:56,884
Mrs. McNally!! Mr. McNally!!
Mr. McNally!! Mr. McNally!!

535
00:50:58,555 --> 00:51:01,991
What's wrong Mr. Sahai?
Is Michelle all right?

536
00:51:02,192 --> 00:51:05,889
Michelle. Michelle she...
Mrs. McNally. She knows, she knows.

537
00:51:06,096 --> 00:51:07,120
She knows the meaning of words.

538
00:51:07,330 --> 00:51:10,356
She actually. Actually
knows the meaning of words.

539
00:51:10,567 --> 00:51:12,330
Look. Look!

540
00:51:15,305 --> 00:51:20,333
Yes, Michelle...
Mother. Mother...

541
00:51:37,994 --> 00:51:38,551
Maa...

542
00:51:52,676 --> 00:51:53,506
Mother

543
00:51:54,678 --> 00:51:55,269
Maa...

544
00:51:56,079 --> 00:51:57,376
Once more

545
00:51:59,249 --> 00:51:59,977
Ma...

546
00:52:05,322 --> 00:52:06,482
Pa... Pa...

547
00:52:47,303 --> 00:52:53,731
This is 'Teacher'. "Tea... cher"

548
00:52:57,714 --> 00:53:06,679
Tee... Tee

549
00:53:08,057 --> 00:53:10,423
Yes... Yes

550
00:53:10,727 --> 00:53:12,854
Yes, he's your Tee

551
00:53:31,247 --> 00:53:32,544
Dear Ms. Nair...

552
00:53:38,555 --> 00:53:40,147
You'll be happy to know...

553
00:53:43,259 --> 00:53:50,495
that I have... I have...

554
00:54:18,194 --> 00:54:21,391
"That day you had won your
first battle over my darkness."

555
00:54:23,166 --> 00:54:24,963
"But today you don't
remember anything."

556
00:54:26,469 --> 00:54:28,403
"Now I will fight
against your darkness."

557
00:54:29,739 --> 00:54:33,903
"I'll teach you everything
you taught me"

558
00:55:34,070 --> 00:55:37,562
"Water. The first word
that you taught me..."

559
00:55:38,141 --> 00:55:40,575
"and after that..."

560
00:55:41,577 --> 00:55:47,482
"you typed every little
detail on my hand..."

561
00:55:47,984 --> 00:55:51,647
"like a maestro playing a symphony"

562
00:55:54,791 --> 00:55:55,519
Cathy!

563
00:55:56,559 --> 00:55:59,187
Martha... Martha!
When did you return from London?

564
00:55:59,395 --> 00:56:03,354
Oh! It's so good to see you.
Merry Christmas.

565
00:56:05,668 --> 00:56:09,229
Mr. McNally...
- Coming, Mr Sahai. Just a moment

566
00:56:10,073 --> 00:56:15,033
I'd like you to meet Mr. Fernandez,
principal of the King Edward University.

567
00:56:15,244 --> 00:56:17,735
I want Michelle to study
in their college

568
00:56:17,947 --> 00:56:19,710
It's an honor to meet you,
Mr. Fernandez.

569
00:56:19,916 --> 00:56:20,541
It's a pleasure sir.

570
00:56:21,050 --> 00:56:22,711
I don't believe how time
has passed, Martha

571
00:56:22,919 --> 00:56:26,480
Let me prove it to you...
Hello... Come

572
00:56:30,026 --> 00:56:35,020
Did you recognize her?
My younger daughter, Sara

573
00:56:35,732 --> 00:56:38,633
Sara, this is aunt Martha,
an old friend of mine

574
00:56:38,835 --> 00:56:39,301
Oh! Hello, aunt Martha.
I've heard so...

575
00:56:39,502 --> 00:56:41,902
But where is my dear Michelle?
I can't wait to see her

576
00:56:42,105 --> 00:56:43,868
Ah Michelle.
Have you seen Michelle?

577
00:56:44,507 --> 00:56:50,377
Err! Yes... I think
she's inside, excuse me.

578
00:56:53,049 --> 00:56:54,209
Come... we'll go look for her.

579
00:57:23,880 --> 00:57:24,778
Ah! There she is

580
00:58:21,504 --> 00:58:25,406
Mr. Sahai. Look at that girl.
She can't hear or see,

581
00:58:25,608 --> 00:58:28,600
And still... just look at her,
it's wonderful.

582
00:58:30,646 --> 00:58:32,136
That's Michelle McNally...

583
00:58:34,784 --> 00:58:38,686
the girl I was talking about.
- That's impossible Mr. Sahai.

584
00:58:38,888 --> 00:58:42,824
Impossible is a word that I have
never taught her Mr. Fernandez.

585
00:58:43,392 --> 00:58:45,587
There are special schools
for such children...

586
00:58:46,095 --> 00:58:48,427
where they are taught many things.

587
00:58:50,132 --> 00:58:54,034
To make baskets, weave carpets...

588
00:58:55,338 --> 00:59:00,366
Have you heard of a girl like Michelle
getting admission in a normal college?

589
00:59:00,576 --> 00:59:03,602
No, but I would love to.

590
00:59:03,813 --> 00:59:06,145
How will she understand the lectures?

591
00:59:06,349 --> 00:59:11,446
I will sit with her in the classroom.
She will learn everything through signs

592
00:59:11,687 --> 00:59:13,882
Every word, every letter.

593
00:59:16,158 --> 00:59:21,994
Michelle... meet your Principal

594
00:59:27,970 --> 00:59:33,602
Yes yes... I've told him... you
want admission in arts, not science

595
00:59:34,510 --> 00:59:38,674
Mr. Sahai I will have to consult
the trustees on this.

596
00:59:38,881 --> 00:59:43,978
You get few chances for good deeds.

597
00:59:44,554 --> 00:59:47,546
And I hope that you will
not lose this opportunity.

598
00:59:50,560 --> 00:59:51,219
Cheers?

599
00:59:53,896 --> 00:59:59,528
Mr. Sahai, you know this university
is for normal students.

600
01:00:00,069 --> 01:00:02,697
But because of your faith
in Michelle...

601
01:00:02,905 --> 01:00:04,839
and because we believe
you are a good teacher...

602
01:00:05,041 --> 01:00:08,238
We will interview Michelle.
- Thank you.

603
01:00:08,511 --> 01:00:10,877
But today, you cannot
interpret for Michelle.

604
01:00:11,280 --> 01:00:16,411
We have called a special teacher,
who doesn't know either of you.

605
01:00:16,719 --> 01:00:17,845
She will interpret.

606
01:00:18,054 --> 01:00:20,750
They will interview you.
Another interpreter, not me, ok?

607
01:00:27,897 --> 01:00:29,364
Ah, there she is.

608
01:00:33,536 --> 01:00:34,093
Mrs Nair?

609
01:00:34,737 --> 01:00:37,205
Welcome Ms. Nair, meet Mr. Sahai.

610
01:00:37,940 --> 01:00:39,202
Hello, Ms. Nair.
- Hello.

611
01:00:39,408 --> 01:00:40,534
Light

612
01:00:50,653 --> 01:00:53,713
Are you ready for the interview?

613
01:00:56,092 --> 01:00:57,116
We're ready, Sir.

614
01:01:00,630 --> 01:01:02,655
Why does she want to study?

615
01:01:03,132 --> 01:01:05,464
Why do you want to study?

616
01:01:07,169 --> 01:01:10,400
I want to study... and learn...

617
01:01:10,973 --> 01:01:16,775
so that I may live with dignity,
with independence... and to be alive.

618
01:01:17,613 --> 01:01:19,240
How many oceans are
there in the world?

619
01:01:19,448 --> 01:01:22,508
How many oceans are
there in the world?

620
01:01:24,086 --> 01:01:30,924
For me every drop of water is an ocean

621
01:01:31,127 --> 01:01:35,587
She is not answering my question.
How many oceans are there in the world?

622
01:01:35,798 --> 01:01:39,256
They want a straight answer
to their question

623
01:01:46,108 --> 01:01:50,101
If we are in India,
on which side will America be?

624
01:01:50,312 --> 01:01:52,712
If you are in India,
which side is America?

625
01:02:12,735 --> 01:02:19,470
The world is round.
So America can be on any side.

626
01:02:22,244 --> 01:02:26,146
What does knowledge mean to her?
- What does knowledge mean to you?

627
01:02:29,018 --> 01:02:31,578
Knowledge... is everything

628
01:02:32,521 --> 01:02:40,394
Knowledge is spirit, wisdom,
courage, light, sound.

629
01:02:42,064 --> 01:02:45,227
Knowledge is my Bible, God...

630
01:02:46,702 --> 01:02:47,828
Tee!

631
01:02:48,337 --> 01:02:53,934
...knowledge is my teacher
- Bravo! Excellent.

632
01:02:59,715 --> 01:03:01,182
Congratulations, Mr. Sahai.

633
01:03:01,851 --> 01:03:05,184
Your student is now a
part of our university.

634
01:03:10,392 --> 01:03:14,021
Thank you... Thank you

635
01:03:22,571 --> 01:03:23,868
I answered every question they asked.

636
01:03:24,974 --> 01:03:30,139
Michelle looks so happy today Paul.
Can't stop talking about the interview

637
01:03:31,413 --> 01:03:33,540
She hasn't stopped smiling all day.

638
01:03:33,749 --> 01:03:38,152
Why not? A girl who couldn't
sit at the dining table...

639
01:03:38,988 --> 01:03:44,051
has a seat in the university today.
Unbelievable.

640
01:03:44,260 --> 01:03:51,223
Can you imagine? Can you imagine the day
when we see Michelle as a graduate?

641
01:03:51,834 --> 01:03:55,565
Ah, it's going to be such a
special day, isn't it Sara?

642
01:03:57,106 --> 01:03:58,232
Yes, of course, mama.

643
01:03:59,008 --> 01:04:01,909
Whatever Michelle does is always special.
Isn't it?

644
01:04:03,245 --> 01:04:05,406
Excuse me;
I need to finish my sketch.

645
01:04:13,355 --> 01:04:15,084
Good evening Sara.
- Good evening.

646
01:04:15,624 --> 01:04:19,583
Mr. Sahai, congratulations.
You have performed yet...

647
01:04:19,795 --> 01:04:23,754
another miracle.
Still a long way to go, Mr. McNally

648
01:04:24,600 --> 01:04:27,865
The journey has just begun.

649
01:04:30,806 --> 01:04:31,773
Teacher!

650
01:04:35,811 --> 01:04:39,269
She's been waiting for
her gift for so long.

651
01:04:51,327 --> 01:04:52,794
What is this?

652
01:04:54,563 --> 01:04:58,021
Your friend, for... life.

653
01:04:58,667 --> 01:05:03,536
I don't need

654
01:05:05,007 --> 01:05:06,474
I don't want to be dependent on this.

655
01:05:08,677 --> 01:05:12,909
This will not make you dependent.

656
01:05:14,483 --> 01:05:19,614
It will make you independent.
Do you understand?

657
01:05:55,624 --> 01:05:57,615
"It was the beginning of a new life..."

658
01:05:58,260 --> 01:06:01,195
"a new feeling, a new horizon..."

659
01:06:01,897 --> 01:06:03,364
"You had faith in me..."

660
01:06:03,899 --> 01:06:05,867
"and I had faith in my wings."

661
01:06:06,268 --> 01:06:09,533
Remember how happy I was
that day?

662
01:06:19,581 --> 01:06:23,108
Is it wise to let Michelle live alone?

663
01:06:23,319 --> 01:06:26,220
She is not alone;
Mrs. Gomes will also live here.

664
01:06:26,422 --> 01:06:28,390
I will also live next door.

665
01:06:29,124 --> 01:06:34,391
University is close by,
she will meet new people.

666
01:06:34,663 --> 01:06:39,259
Besides, we can't protect
her all her life.

667
01:06:39,468 --> 01:06:40,730
Don't worry. She'll be fine!

668
01:06:40,936 --> 01:06:42,233
What's wrong with you, Sara? Huh?

669
01:06:42,438 --> 01:06:44,303
We were all just laughing
now suddenly you're fighting.

670
01:06:44,506 --> 01:06:47,236
It's very irritating, mama.
Anything that I put anywhere...

671
01:06:47,443 --> 01:06:48,842
she picks it up and puts it
somewhere else.

672
01:06:49,812 --> 01:06:51,404
Ma, I love her very much,
I really do.

673
01:06:51,613 --> 01:06:53,911
But... Please... leave me
out of this. Ok?

674
01:06:54,450 --> 01:06:57,248
She's very excited, sweetie.
Please understand

675
01:06:57,453 --> 01:06:59,978
I understand everything.
It's always about her, right?

676
01:07:00,189 --> 01:07:03,352
Her excitement, her happiness, she's
the one who means everything to you

677
01:07:03,826 --> 01:07:07,557
