Thirty words, my foot!

743
01:13:39,654 --> 01:13:43,146
Pass?
- No fail.

744
01:13:49,097 --> 01:13:53,500
No, not in one or two subjects,
you have failed in all of them.

745
01:14:19,528 --> 01:14:23,362
"People celebrate success
but we celebrated failure"

746
01:14:24,766 --> 01:14:27,701
"While eating ice cream
you told me the story of the spider"

747
01:14:28,603 --> 01:14:31,037
"Who after a lot of tries
made her home."

748
01:14:31,773 --> 01:14:34,867
"After all, failure is
the first step towards success..."

749
01:14:35,911 --> 01:14:38,903
"but for me these steps
were never-ending."

750
01:14:45,654 --> 01:14:48,919
Mr. Sahai, how are you?
How is Michelle?

751
01:14:49,791 --> 01:14:52,726
She's all right,
her results have come out.

752
01:14:53,295 --> 01:14:54,159
And what happened?

753
01:14:55,630 --> 01:14:57,564
She has failed again.

754
01:14:59,634 --> 01:15:03,229
But she said that
her papers were easy.

755
01:15:03,438 --> 01:15:08,569
She lied, so she could
enjoy her holidays

756
01:15:11,179 --> 01:15:16,310
But you said that only after falling
can a person rise higher.

757
01:15:18,253 --> 01:15:22,417
Before I fall, I want her
to learn how to fly.

758
01:15:23,525 --> 01:15:28,428
I'm getting old, you know?

759
01:15:28,663 --> 01:15:32,099
Oh no...
- What happened?

760
01:15:32,534 --> 01:15:37,164
Michelle has failed again?
- Yes Paul. I'm worried.

761
01:15:37,506 --> 01:15:38,473
I think Mr Sahai...

762
01:15:41,643 --> 01:15:46,444
Ma... I want to come home.

763
01:15:51,620 --> 01:15:56,785
Ma, I failed.

764
01:15:59,728 --> 01:16:10,696
Teacher shouted at me.

765
01:16:11,540 --> 01:16:12,973
I love you, my baby, I love you.

766
01:16:37,098 --> 01:16:39,498
I was told you were looking
for me Mr. Fernandez

767
01:16:40,335 --> 01:16:44,829
Ah Mr. Sahai, please come in.
I have been waiting for you all day...

768
01:16:46,007 --> 01:16:50,000
I want to share my biggest
achievement with you.

769
01:16:50,679 --> 01:16:52,112
Please have a seat.

770
01:16:56,585 --> 01:17:02,353
Mr. Sahai Michelle has been studying
in the same class for 2 years.

771
01:17:03,258 --> 01:17:06,091
So I thought I would do
something to... help her.

772
01:17:09,764 --> 01:17:13,029
First year Arts, entirely in Braille.

773
01:17:14,769 --> 01:17:20,105
You had once said very few chances
are given for doing good deeds.

774
01:17:20,809 --> 01:17:25,041
I'm happy that you haven't
wasted this chance.

775
01:17:25,981 --> 01:17:28,643
Now no one can stop Michelle
from going ahead. Thank you.

776
01:17:28,883 --> 01:17:33,047
Not at all... It's my duty,
my pleasure, my pride.

777
01:17:37,158 --> 01:17:38,318
I trust that was all right?

778
01:17:46,501 --> 01:17:47,729
Is anything the matter?

779
01:17:50,905 --> 01:17:53,305
Then the books, Mr. Sahai.
Please take them to Michelle.

780
01:17:59,614 --> 01:18:01,582
How do I go out?

781
01:18:04,185 --> 01:18:07,586
How... how do I go out?

782
01:18:08,857 --> 01:18:10,290
I beg your pardon?

783
01:18:10,859 --> 01:18:13,419
The way to go out?

784
01:18:14,429 --> 01:18:16,954
The door, Mr. Sahai...
it's right behind you.

785
01:18:17,365 --> 01:18:18,764
Exactly the way you came in.

786
01:18:22,804 --> 01:18:23,600
Yes...

787
01:18:27,776 --> 01:18:30,438
Mr. Sahai, is everything all right?

788
01:18:48,730 --> 01:18:50,459
Tee... cher...

789
01:19:50,625 --> 01:19:52,354
"New feelings were arising with age..."

790
01:19:53,027 --> 01:19:54,927
"something that I couldn't understand"

791
01:19:55,964 --> 01:19:59,024
"I knew no one besides you teacher"

792
01:20:01,035 --> 01:20:04,436
"That's why I thought of another
relationship with you teacher"

793
01:20:05,540 --> 01:20:07,269
"Was it wrong for me to think this way?"

794
01:20:09,144 --> 01:20:10,543
"A lot was changing..."

795
01:20:11,412 --> 01:20:15,371
"but my failure was constant"

796
01:20:22,490 --> 01:20:24,890
Time up, Michelle... time up.

797
01:20:25,426 --> 01:20:27,621
Michelle, you've already
had extra time.

798
01:20:28,396 --> 01:20:31,388
Michelle... I'll take
the paper out then.

799
01:20:34,269 --> 01:20:35,566
No... no...
- Please...

800
01:20:35,770 --> 01:20:36,737
Leave it...
- Please...

801
01:20:36,938 --> 01:20:40,465
Leave it... no... leave it...

802
01:20:41,576 --> 01:20:43,908
Knowing the answers is not enough...

803
01:20:44,112 --> 01:20:48,105
You have let me down completely.
I am angry... I am very angry...

804
01:20:49,117 --> 01:20:52,416
no... knowing the
answers is not enough...

805
01:20:52,620 --> 01:20:54,645
you need to put them down
on paper too, understand?

806
01:21:01,629 --> 01:21:03,324
Don't just stand there
like a failure!

807
01:21:07,535 --> 01:21:10,003
It's all right.
- No. It's not all right, Mrs. McNally.

808
01:21:10,605 --> 01:21:12,436
It's not only her failure,
it's mine too.

809
01:21:12,941 --> 01:21:15,239
This is the third year in a row
that she's failed.

810
01:21:15,710 --> 01:21:17,439
For three years we have been doing
those same lessons.

811
01:21:17,812 --> 01:21:20,474
She's just too slow at typing.

812
01:21:20,982 --> 01:21:22,847
Hey, Michelle... Michelle...

813
01:21:23,184 --> 01:21:24,446
Where do you think you are going?

814
01:21:24,652 --> 01:21:28,110
Leave this bag...
Leave it, leave it...

815
01:21:28,389 --> 01:21:29,253
Leave this bag!

816
01:21:29,457 --> 01:21:32,017
Enough! I want to go home.

817
01:21:32,227 --> 01:21:34,286
No. No... you're not going anywhere.

818
01:21:34,495 --> 01:21:36,019
I don't want to stay.
I don't want to study.

819
01:21:36,231 --> 01:21:39,792
No... no... You will stay...
you will study. You understand?

820
01:21:40,001 --> 01:21:42,799
You will study. In three years even
the Braille letters have worn out...

821
01:21:43,004 --> 01:21:46,804
but nothing has entered your brain.
- Let her be, Mr. Sahai!

822
01:21:47,041 --> 01:21:49,805
Mrs. McNally, I haven't spent

823
01:21:50,078 --> 01:21:51,978
I'm not going to allow her
to be a failure.

824
01:21:52,247 --> 01:21:54,306
Hey... come here... you...
come here...

825
01:21:54,515 --> 01:21:56,210
Listen, you will...
you will not...

826
01:21:56,317 --> 01:22:01,220
you will not run away from failure.
Understand? Not run away from failure!

827
01:22:02,690 --> 01:22:06,387
Michelle... what is this? Don't you
dare disrespect a book!

828
01:22:06,594 --> 01:22:08,323
Pick it up... Come on.
Pick it up., pick up the book...

829
01:22:08,529 --> 01:22:10,997
pick up the book... Michelle...
Michelle...

830
01:22:11,366 --> 01:22:12,993
Pick up the book...

831
01:22:14,035 --> 01:22:14,660
Stop it

832
01:22:25,213 --> 01:22:27,511
As long as I am alive,
you will study.

833
01:22:28,049 --> 01:22:30,677
I don't want to learn.

834
01:22:30,885 --> 01:22:33,376
Yes! You will learn.
You will graduate.

835
01:22:33,721 --> 01:22:36,383
The black robe. Our dream...

836
01:22:36,891 --> 01:22:41,851
I don't want a robe.
My world is black

837
01:22:42,063 --> 01:22:47,262
No. Your world... your world is
not black. It is full of light!

838
01:22:47,468 --> 01:22:52,201
My world is black, black, black!

839
01:22:52,407 --> 01:22:55,865
Black... black...

840
01:23:24,272 --> 01:23:28,402

841
01:23:29,677 --> 01:23:30,905
in less than 2 minutes.

842
01:23:34,615 --> 01:23:37,584
She's not slow anymore Mrs McNally

843
01:23:39,854 --> 01:23:42,414
Time for celebration.

844
01:23:43,758 --> 01:23:47,626
Time for... an icecream, my dear

845
01:23:49,664 --> 01:23:51,632
Ice-cream?
- Yes...

846
01:23:52,133 --> 01:24:01,166
Mrs. McNally. Life is an ice-cream.
Enjoy it before it melts.

847
01:24:16,124 --> 01:24:17,284
Can I have two?

848
01:24:20,461 --> 01:24:21,860
Ice creams, of course...

849
01:24:28,302 --> 01:24:30,099
Sir... ice-cream...

850
01:24:32,573 --> 01:24:33,301
Ice-cream sir.

851
01:24:40,848 --> 01:24:42,645
What happened?
- Tee...

852
01:24:43,518 --> 01:24:44,314
What's wrong with you?

853
01:24:48,689 --> 01:24:49,656
Your change, sir.

854
01:24:51,492 --> 01:24:52,652
Sir, your change?

855
01:25:23,925 --> 01:25:32,196
Tee... Tee...

856
01:25:37,572 --> 01:25:42,202
tee... tee... tee...

857
01:25:53,087 --> 01:25:59,890
Are you alright?
Call for a doctor!

858
01:26:04,765 --> 01:26:05,561
Mr. Sahai?

859
01:26:08,102 --> 01:26:09,069
Mr. Sahai?

860
01:26:10,638 --> 01:26:13,198
You are here...
I've been looking for you.

861
01:26:14,609 --> 01:26:15,234
Yes?

862
01:26:16,310 --> 01:26:17,641
Don't you recognize me?

863
01:26:18,346 --> 01:26:19,779
It's me... Fernandez

864
01:26:22,783 --> 01:26:23,909
Michelle's Principal.

865
01:26:25,486 --> 01:26:29,217
Oh... yes. Of course.
I'll get Michelle for you.

866
01:26:29,457 --> 01:26:32,153
Michelle!
- Michelle can't hear, Mr. Sahai.

867
01:26:38,599 --> 01:26:41,568
I'll just call her.

868
01:26:44,772 --> 01:26:47,605
Mrs. Gomes!!!
- Michelle is not at home.

869
01:26:54,315 --> 01:26:55,009
She's here.

870
01:27:08,496 --> 01:27:12,125
To forget my name,
to forget the door...

871
01:27:12,833 --> 01:27:16,769
all this is fine... but to forget
Michelle like this...

872
01:27:17,905 --> 01:27:19,839
something is seriously wrong,
Mr. Sahai.

873
01:27:20,508 --> 01:27:23,341
I really think you should
get some help and see a doctor...

874
01:27:26,681 --> 01:27:27,807
Good night. Mr. Sahai.

875
01:28:08,289 --> 01:28:11,349
I'm... sorry.

876
01:28:14,729 --> 01:28:16,390
It's ok.
- It's ok.

877
01:28:17,932 --> 01:28:19,900
Don't ever forget me...

878
01:28:27,241 --> 01:28:27,866
I promise...

879
01:28:29,243 --> 01:28:30,870
I will never forget... you

880
01:28:32,713 --> 01:28:35,443
You worry about me?

881
01:28:39,153 --> 01:28:43,021
No. Don't... worry about me...

882
01:28:44,925 --> 01:28:49,919
just... getting old.

883
01:28:53,134 --> 01:28:55,967
No... Don't worry.

884
01:28:59,106 --> 01:29:01,939
Go to... sleep.

885
01:29:06,180 --> 01:29:08,944
Sing you... a lullaby...

886
01:29:10,718 --> 01:29:12,242
No, I can't sing...

887
01:29:27,101 --> 01:29:33,939
Hush, my baby.
On the treetop.

888
01:29:35,976 --> 01:29:42,404
When the wind blows,
the cradle will rock...

889
01:29:44,385 --> 01:29:46,615
hush my baby...

890
01:29:48,055 --> 01:29:50,990
"A storm had scattered my dreams"

891
01:29:51,659 --> 01:29:54,492
"All those dreams those
were most dear to me"

892
01:29:56,530 --> 01:29:59,465
"That day was the first time
I felt fear..."

893
01:30:00,735 --> 01:30:04,796
"how would I live
if you forget me?"

894
01:30:07,775 --> 01:30:09,970
What happened now?
- She doesn't want to come downstairs

895
01:30:10,144 --> 01:30:12,635
She is feeling awkward to come
in front of your in-laws.

896
01:30:12,847 --> 01:30:14,246
She thinks she'll spoil the evening.

897
01:30:14,615 --> 01:30:16,310
Then why did she bother
coming till here?

898
01:30:16,517 --> 01:30:17,484
Stop it Sara!!!

899
01:30:18,119 --> 01:30:22,180
She's worried about
Mr. Sahai's health, please...

900
01:30:22,757 --> 01:30:25,225
it really hurts me to see
the two of you fight like this...

901
01:30:25,993 --> 01:30:27,517
now you get her ready
and you bring her down.

902
01:30:27,728 --> 01:30:28,888
I have a lot of work to finish...

903
01:30:34,802 --> 01:30:38,670
Michelle, I'm requesting you...

904
01:30:39,273 --> 01:30:42,208
till now whatever you did
was special.

905
01:30:42,977 --> 01:30:46,413
But today is a very
special day for me.

906
01:30:47,114 --> 01:30:51,107
I'm in love and I am getting
engaged before you.

907
01:30:51,786 --> 01:30:53,276
I know this could upset you.

908
01:30:53,721 --> 01:30:56,315
Maybe this evening will
never come in your life

909
01:30:56,891 --> 01:30:59,485
And you may be feeling that
you will never fall in love.

910
01:31:01,362 --> 01:31:03,853
I hope you will.
I really do...

911
01:31:04,398 --> 01:31:06,366
but, until then...

912
01:31:06,734 --> 01:31:12,138
please don't... spoil. My. Evening. Ok?

913
01:31:22,917 --> 01:31:26,375
I am very happy today because all the
people I care about in the world...

914
01:31:26,587 --> 01:31:31,047
are in this room. On this occasion,
I'd love to say a few words.

915
01:31:37,765 --> 01:31:40,962
I'm a very lucky girl that
I got parents like you.

916
01:31:41,769 --> 01:31:43,168
And a sister like Michelle.

917
01:31:44,104 --> 01:31:46,732
I haven't been the best
daughter or the best sister.

918
01:31:47,107 --> 01:31:49,632
But I want to tell you all
I that really love you very much.

919
01:31:51,445 --> 01:31:52,742
And I love this house.

920
01:31:53,948 --> 01:31:55,506
There are so many memories here.

921
01:31:56,951 --> 01:31:59,579
I remember one time Michelle
and I were playing outside.

922
01:31:59,787 --> 01:32:02,085
We were running through
the grass holding hands.

923
01:32:02,790 --> 01:32:07,090
And while running, both of us fell
down and both of us started crying.

924
01:32:07,628 --> 01:32:14,591
Mama and Papa came running outside and
picked up Michelle and left me outside...

925
01:32:16,136 --> 01:32:18,866
and there I was...
with my arms stretched out.

926
01:32:19,139 --> 01:32:20,003
Waiting.

927
01:32:22,142 --> 01:32:23,268
I'm still waiting.

928
01:32:26,146 --> 01:32:30,446
As a child. I...
I used to be so angry with her.

929
01:32:31,986 --> 01:32:35,114
The amount I loved her the
same amount I was jealous of her...

930
01:32:35,656 --> 01:32:38,124
whatever food I didn't like,
I'd feed her.

931
01:32:40,160 --> 01:32:43,459
I used to wake Michelle in the
middle of the night and ask her...

932
01:32:44,164 --> 01:32:48,032
do you want to drink water? Michelle
used to nod her head and say yes...

933
01:32:49,503 --> 01:32:51,471
and I used to turn my head
and go back to sleep.

934
01:32:53,841 --> 01:32:55,638
She would wait for me
all night long.

935
01:33:00,681 --> 01:33:02,148
I can't believe I did that.

936
01:33:06,520 --> 01:33:07,714
Can you Marc?

937
01:33:12,192 --> 01:33:16,060
For all those things that I did,
and all the misplaced...

938
01:33:16,864 --> 01:33:19,731
anger... I'd like to say I'm sorry.

939
01:33:22,202 --> 01:33:23,499
Did I say something wrong?

940
01:33:24,371 --> 01:33:26,339
Then please let me finish.
- I don't want to listen,

941
01:33:26,540 --> 01:33:27,734
It's important to me. Michelle.

942
01:33:42,056 --> 01:33:45,685
Michelle...
- Enough!!!!

943
01:33:54,401 --> 01:33:55,527
Sit down.

944
01:33:57,905 --> 01:33:59,964
SIT... DOWN.

945
01:34:15,756 --> 01:34:17,781
For this joyous and
eventful evening...

946
01:34:19,927 --> 01:34:23,385
Michelle had prepared
a speech for Sara,

947
01:34:24,098 --> 01:34:29,730
I would read and Michelle
would sign...

948
01:34:30,938 --> 01:34:35,238
but I don't think that Michelle
is in any mood for signs.

949
01:34:36,944 --> 01:34:43,076
It's important however, that we
should all hear what she said.

950
01:34:45,452 --> 01:34:51,755
"I was eight years old, wild, violent
always angry at life."

951
01:34:54,962 --> 01:34:58,762
"I felt that I would never experience
the beautiful moments of life."

952
01:34:59,967 --> 01:35:03,095
"Then mother put Sara in my arms
for the first time..."

953
01:35:10,310 --> 01:35:15,612
"and then I knew that I'd see the world
through Sara's eyes."

954
01:35:16,817 --> 01:35:22,722
"Ma says, that I couldn't
stop smiling all day."

955
01:35:28,996 --> 01:35:32,295
"Sara shared all her happiness
with me..."

956
01:35:33,333 --> 01:35:36,530
"she would hold my hand
and take me everywhere."

957
01:35:36,837 --> 01:35:39,533
"When Ma wasn't around
she would feed me..."

958
01:35:40,007 --> 01:35:44,068
"she would wake me at night
and ask me if I wanted water."

959
01:35:49,516 --> 01:35:52,144
"You were the voice
to my silent fingers."

960
01:35:54,354 --> 01:35:56,879
"I am so looking forward
to your wedding day."

961
01:35:59,026 --> 01:36:00,323
"I'll dress up beautifully that day."

962
01:36:09,203 --> 01:36:11,569
"I may never be the bride,
but I will still be the bridesmaid."

963
01:36:16,543 --> 01:36:24,109
"Do teach Marc how to sign,
I have lots to complain about you."

964
01:36:26,720 --> 01:36:29,245
"Thank you for allowing me
to be your bridesmaid, Sara."

965
01:36:30,724 --> 01:36:38,927
"I promise I will not cry... as you
walk with Marc towards a new life."

966
01:36:56,583 --> 01:36:58,949
So on this happy note...

967
01:37:02,256 --> 01:37:03,280
a toast...

968
01:37:06,093 --> 01:37:08,823
for Sara and Marc

969
01:38:07,821 --> 01:38:11,450
Do you, Marc Philip Bragger,
take Sara Maria McNally...

970
01:38:11,658 --> 01:38:15,116
to be you're lawfully wedded wife?
- I do.

971
01:38:15,662 --> 01:38:17,960
Marc... says yes.

972
01:38:18,165 --> 01:38:22,966
Do you, Sara Maria McNally...
- Now the priest is asking Sara...

973
01:38:23,170 --> 01:38:25,035
take Marc Philip Bragger to be
your lawfully wedded husband?

974
01:38:25,239 --> 01:38:26,797
If she agrees...
- I do.

975
01:38:27,007 --> 01:38:28,907
Sara says..."Yes".

976
01:38:29,843 --> 01:38:32,710
I declare you to be man and wife

977
01:38:35,849 --> 01:38:39,148
Now they are exchanging rings.

978
01:38:39,353 --> 01:38:40,650
You may now kiss the bride.

979
01:38:40,854 --> 01:38:47,316
The priest has asked them
to kiss as man and wife.

980
01:38:51,031 --> 01:38:54,831
On the cheek?
- No, no, not on the cheek. On the lips.

981
01:39:44,251 --> 01:39:45,377
Tee...

982
01:39:54,261 --> 01:39:55,125
Te...

983
01:40:05,105 --> 01:40:07,903
What are you doing here?

984
01:40:09,609 --> 01:40:11,907
Wanted... to talk.

985
01:40:28,128 --> 01:40:31,928
Do you love... me?

986
01:40:41,808 --> 01:40:44,606
I'm suffering...

987
01:40:49,983 --> 01:40:55,046
I understand that you are suffering...

988
01:40:58,658 --> 01:41:05,063
I may never know... what it is
to... love... a man.

989
01:41:09,836 --> 01:41:20,644
Maybe you will never
experience physical love

990
01:41:26,686 --> 01:41:27,550
but...

991
01:41:33,860 --> 01:41:38,820
will you kiss me once...

992
01:41:43,370 --> 01:41:44,166
please?

993
01:43:18,465 --> 01:43:19,432
Tee...

994
01:43:24,804 --> 01:43:25,600
Teee...

995
01:43:26,806 --> 01:43:30,003
"In giving me dignity
as a woman..."

996
01:43:30,477 --> 01:43:33,776
"you lost all dignity
as a teacher."

997
01:43:34,814 --> 01:43:37,442
"I realized that
I had asked too much."

998
01:43:38,318 --> 01:43:39,342
"I made a mistake."

999
01:43:40,487 --> 01:43:42,955
"You didn't even give me a chance
to ask for your forgiveness."

1000
01:43:44,324 --> 01:43:45,621
"I'm leaving"

1001
01:43:46,826 --> 01:43:51,695
"Like your walking-stick,
never forget one thing"

1002
01:43:52,832 --> 01:43:58,134
"Darkness is desperately trying
to engulf you"

1003
01:43:59,172 --> 01:44:01,572
"But you must always
walk towards light"

1004
01:44:02,509 --> 01:44:06,912
"Every step of yours, filled with hope,
will keep me alive, Michelle"

1005
01:44:20,527 --> 01:44:22,825
"Once again light transcended
into darkness..."

1006
01:44:24,197 --> 01:44:26,722
"and sound into silence."

1007
01:44:27,367 --> 01:44:32,669
"For twelve years
I walked the path you showed me..."

1008
01:44:33,707 --> 01:44:35,834
"alone in the darkness."

1009
01:44:37,877 --> 01:44:41,938
"When after twelve years I had
found you near the same fountain..."

1010
01:44:42,716 --> 01:44:45,617
"and today after 12 days
this mark sheet."

1011
01:44:46,052 --> 01:44:48,680
"I'm now a graduate in the arts."

1012
01:44:49,723 --> 01:44:52,283
"I want you to be the first one
to hear the good news"

1013
01:44:53,226 --> 01:44:56,525
Mr. Sahai this is your bed,
please lie down.

1014
01:44:56,896 --> 01:45:00,696
Please... that's it. Mr. Sahai...

1015
01:45:00,900 --> 01:45:03,869
This is your bed, Mr. Sahai!

1016
01:45:04,070 --> 01:45:04,866
Nurse!

1017
01:45:06,239 --> 01:45:07,206
Mr. Sahai...

1018
01:45:08,575 --> 01:45:11,703
please lie down... Mr. Sahai

1019
01:45:29,929 --> 01:45:30,725
Tee...

1020
01:45:48,948 --> 01:45:49,744
Teee!

1021
01:45:50,617 --> 01:45:51,345
Tee...

1022
01:45:54,954 --> 01:45:55,818
Tee!

1023
01:46:32,325 --> 01:46:34,953
"Amidst us today there
is a student..."

1024
01:46:35,161 --> 01:46:38,130
who has set an example
of grit and strength...

1025
01:46:38,665 --> 01:46:43,796
and has proved that
nothing is impossible.

1026
01:46:44,838 --> 01:46:47,466
She is the pride of our university.

1027
01:46:47,674 --> 01:46:51,474
And on this rare achievement, I would
want her to say a few words.

1028
01:46:51,678 --> 01:46:54,738
Ladies and Gentleman - Michelle McNally

1029
01:47:01,688 --> 01:47:03,212
That's my daughter.

1030
01:47:19,539 --> 01:47:21,166
After many attempts...

1031
01:47:22,041 --> 01:47:25,340
the spider, in spite of
falling several times...

1032
01:47:26,045 --> 01:47:27,512
has finally made her home.

1033
01:47:29,215 --> 01:47:31,115
The ant has climbed her mountain.

1034
01:47:32,218 --> 01:47:34,846
A tortoise has crossed the dessert...

1035
01:47:35,722 --> 01:47:39,180
and today Michelle McNally,
has finally become a graduate.

1036
01:47:44,397 --> 01:47:46,865
But there is a difference
between you and me.

1037
01:47:47,066 --> 01:47:51,696
What took you 20 years
has taken me 40.

1038
01:47:52,572 --> 01:47:54,199
But I finally did it!

1039
01:48:02,081 --> 01:48:07,212
As a child, I always
lagged behind others.

1040
01:48:09,923 --> 01:48:14,383
My parents were always ashamed of me.

1041
01:48:15,428 --> 01:48:19,489
Every year I would call home
and say, "Ma, I failed."

1042
01:48:22,435 --> 01:48:23,902
But today I can say...

1043
01:48:24,103 --> 01:48:26,162
"Ma, I passed."

1044
01:48:33,780 --> 01:48:38,240
I know that my parents
are very proud of me.

1045
01:48:39,285 --> 01:48:42,982
Telling the world proudly that
I am their daughter

1046
01:48:43,623 --> 01:48:45,648
Thank you Mama, Papa...

1047
01:48:54,467 --> 01:49:03,398
As a child, I was always
searching for something.

1048
01:49:04,143 --> 01:49:07,112
But in the end,
I would only find darkness.

1049
01:49:08,147 --> 01:49:14,609
One day, my mother put me
in those unknown arms.

1050
01:49:15,989 --> 01:49:19,356
He was different from every one.
He was a magician.

1051
01:49:19,993 --> 01:49:26,557
For years he dragged me from
darkness into the light.

1052
01:49:29,836 --> 01:49:32,566
When it comes to God,
we are all blind.

1053
01:49:33,172 --> 01:49:36,369
None of you have ever
seen Him or heard Him.

1054
01:49:37,677 --> 01:49:43,138
But I have touched God.
I have felt his presence.

1055
01:49:44,517 --> 01:49:48,180
I call him "Tee.

1056
01:49:56,362 --> 01:49:58,262
For me everything was BLACK

1057
01:50:00,700 --> 01:50:06,002
But my teacher taught me
the new meaning of Black

1058
01:50:10,376 --> 01:50:13,937
Black is not only darkness
and suffocation.

1059
01:50:17,216 --> 01:50:19,013
It is the colour of achievement.

1060
01:50:20,386 --> 01:50:21,751
The colour of knowledge.

1061
01:50:24,057 --> 01:50:26,525
The colour of the graduation robe.

1062
01:50:27,226 --> 01:50:29,091
The colour that we all share today.

1063
01:50:31,230 --> 01:50:33,095
But there is a difference
between you and me.

1064
01:50:33,399 --> 01:50:36,630
Today you all wear this
to celebrate graduation.

1065
01:50:37,070 --> 01:50:38,037
But not me.

1066
01:50:40,406 --> 01:50:44,502
Because I want my teacher
to be the first one to see me...

1067
01:50:45,111 --> 01:50:47,545
wear this black robe.

1068
01:50:54,921 --> 01:50:58,880
Every graduation day,
he brought me here.

1069
01:50:59,592 --> 01:51:02,459
Every year, we would stand
near that door...

1070
01:51:02,929 --> 01:51:05,989
and every year he would
write in my hand...

1071
01:51:06,599 --> 01:51:10,729
"One day I want to see you
on that stage Michelle"

1072
01:51:13,773 --> 01:51:15,070
It has taken me 40 years...

1073
01:51:15,274 --> 01:51:17,333
to fulfill his dream.

1074
01:51:18,277 --> 01:51:22,577
And today, for the first time,
I feel my lack of sight.

1075
01:51:23,282 --> 01:51:31,246
Because I want to see my teacher
standing at the door...

1076
01:51:31,457 --> 01:51:33,425
watching me fulfill our dream
with pride

1077
01:51:57,583 --> 01:51:58,550
"Teacher..."

1078
01:53:49,428 --> 01:53:57,233
"Our dream"...Tee... Woah...

1079
01:54:52,491 --> 01:54:53,287
Woah... woah

1080
01:55:03,836 --> 01:55:04,461
Woah

1081
01:55:06,505 --> 01:55:07,631
Woah...

1082
01:55:17,516 --> 01:55:18,483
Tee... Woah

1083
01:55:23,189 --> 01:55:24,053
woah

1084
01:55:40,539 --> 01:55:46,000
"Dear Ms. Nair, you'll be happy to
know that we have come into the light:

1085
01:55:47,380 --> 01:55:52,511
"Today my teacher has remembered
his first word - Water."

1086
01:55:53,886 --> 01:55:55,854
"He is the greatest teacher
in the world..."

1087
01:55:56,222 --> 01:56:00,682
"who has proved again that there is
nothing impossible in this world."

1088
01:56:01,560 --> 01:56:06,190
"Who has taught me that there is so much
happiness in living for someone else"

1089
01:56:06,899 --> 01:56:10,096
"Today is my teacher's
first day at school Miss Nair."

1090
01:56:10,569 --> 01:56:15,199
And his alphabets, just like mine,
will not start with A, B, C, D, and E.

1091
01:56:15,741 --> 01:56:21,043
But with B, L, A, C, K

1092
01:56:22,081 --> 01:56:23,105
"BLACK"